rComments: Cares about his students and always explains everything in depth and thoughtfully. Great Professor.
Dolan's lecture are really engaging and he is lovable. He brings all topics to life. He is very open to new topics when assigning a paper.

The subject matter of Dolan's courses is relevant to our lives. I enjoy listening to him lecture; he does know what he's talking about, and gives ample opportunities with tests and assignments to demonstrate your knowledge.

Hands down, Dolan is the best English professor on campus. He is inspiring, motivating and highly enjoys his job. You will read and write a lot in his classes but it's easy because he teaches everything so clearly. You choose your essay topics, exams are bring your notes exams, he likes in class discussions and participaton. HE IS THE BEST.
Super smart guy, good looking, and he's so into what he's teaching. His enthusiasm makes the class really entertaining. I love his class and would highly recommend this professor.
Super smart guy, good looking, and he's so into what he's teaching. His enthusiasm makes the class really entertaining. I love his class and would highly recommend this professor.
A really great Professor!

I look forward to his lectures, he is VERY intelligent, afterward I find myself thinking about what he's taught - digesting it. His term tests are not difficult if you've done the readings/gone to class - you can bring prepared notes. He is approachable, energetic, remembers names. I love him and I wish he taught more courses. GREAT PROF!
Enthusiastic, clear, articulate. Really interesting course and great lecturer. Whoever thinks he talks slow needs to get their brain checked.
Amazing and engaging lecturer. Really brings the readings to life. He obviously knows his subjects.
Knows what he's talking about. Lecturing style invites students to participate. Approachable. Very flexible professor, but material is usually not easy. Heavy readings.
I usually take courses that Dolan teaches because he really is the best professor on campus. Also the best looking in my opinion!
Coolest professor on campus.
Dolan rocks my world.

I can't understand anyone not wanting to. His enthusiasm is adorable and he will do anything he can to help you and gets excited when students get excited.  He is very flexible - if you don't like the prescribed essay topics he is almost happier to see you branch out. the best prof I had this year and I can't wait to take more classes with him.

He's one of my favorite profs of all time, he's not easy but he's very fair. He never posts notes on the intranet, but if you make an effort so  he actually remembers who you are he'll go out of his way for you! He's also a Harvard graduate so he's very articulate...and yummy!
Boring
Dolan is made of Awesomeness

Great professor! He's very intelligent, has a lot of original ideas plus the nicest Prof I've had. Exams are very fair (just don't miss lectures/do all readings) and no question is a stupid question in his class. He goes out of his way to help his students, plus he's adorable!!
I really did not like his teaching style at all. I found myself bored out of my mind and an completely unmotivated to go to his course. Prof leonard was way better at into to litt.
wow.. what a total hottie... He's so understanding, and just so passionate.. I am SO glad to have taken his courses.. Did I mention his cute little wardrobe.. ;)
best proff ever!! He always has a smile on his face and is always there for help. The most adorable proff in utsc!
man, i love this guy.  seriously, i've had 2 classes with him and he is just a great guy.
HOrrible prof. Some of the most boring lectures I have ever been to. Rambles on & on without much substance to lectures. Do NOT take intro English with him. Wait for Leonard to come back!

Brilliant man, he rambled a lot but I couldn't get enough of it, it was a course where I could actually feel my mind expanding, always recommend it. Plus he's adorable, love his tight pants and his Dalton McGuinty-esque looks :) He's always late, though :D
Great guy. Good listener.  Very passionate.  Learned so much of value in his class.
This class is super boring. I fell asleep through the 2nd lecture. I thought I would enjoy his lecture but he moves way too slow.  Reconsidering my English minor!!
I don't know why, but I like this guy. You can tell he's passionate about what he teaches, and if you pay enough attention in class, you're sure to do well.

You can tell he's nervous when he's at the front of the class, but one of the nicest profs I've encountered yet. Not only does he take the time to learn your name, he'll say hi in the halls, even when you're no longer in his class! Be prepared for a lot of reading with him, however.
such a cool guy, cute too.

I'll try giving you an objective view of Dolan.  His lectures are extremely boring in that he follows the same format every class, however, he does seem to care about what he's doing.  Unless you love the subject intrinsically, you will likely be bored and unstimulated at times, but he definitely isn't terrible.  He's definitely not the best looker
He is horrible. I can't stand him. He acts all nice but he is horrible!

1 of 2 of my fav profs at UofT (the other being Prof Leonard). Prof Dolan is incredibly intelligent and nice (almost to a fault) and passionate about what we read! PLUS he's definitely easy on the eyes ;) If you can't stand slow-talkers, you prob won't like Dolan. But if you can get past his slower pace, what he has to say is so worth the wait!!!!

he's so great...yes he says um a lot and he does sometimes go on tangent, but his brilliance makes up for it....if you sleep through his lectures, you'll miss insights that you have never heard before...i find that other english professors rehash stuff that has been said before...dolan is really original and a very nice person.
Very passionate about what he's talking about.
What are you talking about people, the prof.is the hottest one at school yet!
i still don't have a paper back. he talks slow. tangents are his best friend.

Dolan hot??? i don't think so! He is a good prof. if only he gets past the bad habit of saying "um" like a million times each class. This makes him very unclear, but he is a nice guy, helpful most of the time. And he is the type of Prof. who believes that there is no such thing as a stupid question. Tends to go off topic ALOT!!
a very deceptive guy; superficially friendly but actually very mean; not a good teacher
A brillant man who is passionate about literature.  I loved the course and found the lectures very intersting.  If you attend every class you will certainly get an A.  Bonus: He is so hot!!!

Course material was a little dry but he was genuinely interested which made it easier to listen to. He really cares and is completely understanding and compassionate. I enjoyed the class, although he's probably not for everyone
As mentioned, very slow speaker. Interesting reading material. I recommend going to class because the exam questions/essay questions are straight from lecture examples.

in response to previous posts: he is so not hot. He sounds like the over-voice from "The Wuzzles". He walks back and forth the WHOLE time and he takes forever to get his thought out of his mouth. But he's smart. And nice. Just doesn't strike me as a lit prof.

It's true, we did fall behind everyday, but it was almost impossible to be confused.  he speaks so slowly that you can actually record his lectures word for word, with time to take a hand-stretch break.  Not everyone would like his style, but i thought it was great. he's incredibly compassionate.

His class was AWFUL. He is very redundant, slow, and he falls behind every week. In that sense, he'll give you a lot of extensions as it's usually his fault for not posting the topics. He's a nice man but it's a boring class with godawful material.

just oh so lovely. my favourite prof ever! down to earth, pratical, very interesting, sympathetic, soooo intelligent, very adorable, profoundly articulate, approachable, incredibly funny, and humble. u miss out if u dont at least one course w him!
Dolan is a nice guy! He is very smart and interested in his course material.  He listens well to the opinions of others, and encourages creativity.  And he is a pleasure to look at!!!!!

I learned nothing from this class. He teaches like the stereotypical 90 year old priest  performing a wedding ceremony in a movie (see the Princess Bride). Staccato and slow. A nice man in general though.
Intelligent, articulate, experienced, and genuinely compassionate. Plus, he's just as bogged down in work as the average student, so highly sympathetic to boot! ( adorable, too ;)
Somewhat repetitive but easy to understand. A genuinely nice guy.
